Sequential decision process (e.g., decision tree structure): This subclass is indented under subclass 224.
Subject matter wherein the classification of a pattern* proceeds sequentially through logical stages, each successive stage reducing typically the number of likely choices of pattern* classes, culminating finally in either a definite class assignment for the pattern* or a reject signal.
