Subject matter wherein a different classification principle is utilized at each stage or level.
(1) Note.
For example, given a two-level classifier, the first level might employ a dictionary look-up method, and if no decision is reached at the first level (i.e., no match), the second level is then activated employing a nearest neighborhood method.
