264 Lowpass filter (i.e., for blurring or smoothing): This subclass is indented under subclass 260.
Subject matter wherein high-frequency components of the image are attenuated or eliminated.
(1) Note.
Generally, lowpass filtering blurs edges as it removes small details from the image, reduces noise and bridges small gaps in lines or curves.
Note.
An example of a lowpass filter is the Gaussian filter.
